^-{ An Introduction to Drawing Trumps }
^-|CP||fp||CP|8|at|^B@2^Z@3W|CP||FP||at|elcome everyone. Let's get started. This month's declarer play lesson is on trump management. It builds on last month's lesson, which was on counting winners. In fact, every lesson from here on out is based on that lesson. So, if you were unable to attend last month, I suggest you download Kia's movie from my web site. For those of you who are new to my lessons, go to my web site ^*Hwww.hondobridge.com/ ^*N for lots of free downloads, and to sign up for my weekly emails. |
PG| ***** 3 ***** |


AT|

This month I will focus on when and how to draw trumps. Basically, we are originally taught to draw trumps at the beginning of the hand and that is often very good advice. However, I would say that you should draw trumps immediately about half the time. Your instinct should be to draw trumps, but there are often reasons to delay.|
PG| ***** 4 ***** |


AT|

The advantage, of course, of drawing trumps right away is that you prevent the opponents from trumping your winners. If you have trump length and strength, it is often easy to get the defenders' trump out. However, there are often reasons not to draw trump right away. Probably the most common reason is because you want to trump something in dummy, and if you draw trumps, dummy will not have any left to trump with.|
PG| ***** 5 ***** |


AT|

A second important reason, particularly when you have shorter trumps (eight or seven) and a bad break, is that you don't want to "lose control" of the hand. By losing control I mean the opponents run you out of trump by making you ruff prematurely, and then they can run a long suit. If they run you out of trump, you lose a big advantage. In these situations, sometimes, you have to knock out the opponents' high cards while still retaining your trumps to make sure that does not happen.|
PG| ***** 6 ***** |


AT|

The third reason is for retaining entries. Sometimes you need to keep the trumps because you want to set up a suit and need entries to get to it once it is set up.|
PG| ***** 7 ***** |


